title: Irish flight attendant gets the party started with inflight jig
text:
Irish flight attendant gets the party started with inflight jig Last updated 13:23, October 15 2015 
Inflight entertainment at its best! Posted by Orla O' Brien on Tuesday, October 13, 2015 
We all know planes are usually boring places, but one passenger captured a cute video of some inflight entertainment that would put Air New Zealand's safety videos to shame. 
The impromptu mid-air party broke out during a recent Aer Lingus flight when crew member, Orla O'Brien, joined what appears to be a passenger for a bit of a jig - complete with live Irish fiddle music. 
The good humoured O'Brien shared the video to Facebook with one person commenting " So that's what you get up to up in the clouds. Brilliant Urla." Orla O'Brien/Facebook 
Flight attendant Orla O'Brien has created her own version of 'inflight entertainment'
